9.1 Status API
==============

 -- Function: flycheck-report-status status
     Report Flycheck STATUS.

     STATUS is one of the following symbols:

     ``not-checked''
          The current buffer was not checked.

     ``no-checker''
          Automatic syntax checker selection did not find a suitable
          syntax checker.

     ``running''
          A syntax check is now running in the current buffer.

     ``errored''
          The current syntax check has errored.

     ``finished''
          The current syntax check was finished normally.

     ``interrupted''
          The current syntax check was interrupted.

     ``suspicious''
          The last syntax check had a suspicious result.

     Set *note `flycheck-last-status-change': 8b. and call
     *note `flycheck-status-changed-functions': 59. with STATUS.  Afterwards
     refresh the mode line.

 -- Function: flycheck-report-error
     Report a Flycheck error status.

     Clears all Flycheck errors first, runs
     *note `flycheck-syntax-check-failed-hook': 5c. and reports the status with
     *note `flycheck-report-status': 5a.

 -- Variable: flycheck-last-status-change
          Variable properties: Automatically becomes buffer-local when
          set.

     The last status change in the current buffer.

 -- Function: flycheck-mode-line-status-text &optional status
     Get a text describing STATUS for use in the mode line.

     STATUS defaults to *note `flycheck-last-status-change': 8b. if omitted or
     nil.


